NAME
     fmtoafa - convert a finite state machine to an _a_f_a

SYNOPSIS
     fmtoafa fm

     fmtoafa <fm

DESCRIPTION
     fmtoafa reads in a given finite state machine, convert it to
     an  _a_f_a,  and  then  writes the _a_f_a on the standard ouput in
     bit-wise representation.

     _f_m must  conform  to  the  Grail  format  for  finite  state
     machines.   fmtoafa  doesn't  assume  _f_m  to  be complete or
     deterministic

     The alphabet for the resulting _a_f_a is all the input  symbols
     which appear in instructions of the finite state machine.

EXAMPLES
          % cat testfm2
          (START) |- 1
          1 a 3
          1 b 1
          2 a 3
          2 b 1
          2 c 0
          3 a 3
          3 b 2
          0 a 4
          0 b 4
          0 c 4
          1 c 4
          3 c 4
          4 a 4
          4 b 4
          4 c 4
          0 -| (FINAL)

          % fmtoafa testfm2
          symbols: [a,b,c]
          states:  3
          finals:  2
          head: 7 4
          6 2+7 1
          7 1
          0 1
          0 1
          6 2+7 1
          0 1
          0 1



